The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Mountain Ranch had a population of 223. The population density was {{convert|57.0|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Mountain Ranch was 184 (82.5%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 2 (0.9%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 6 (2.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 9 (4.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 22 (9.9%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 25 persons (11.2%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Mountain Ranch CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0649628 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 106 households, out of which 25 (23.6%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 43 (40.6%) were married-couple households, 12 (11.3%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 25 (23.6%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 26 (24.5%) had a male householder with no partner present. 35 households (33.0%) were one person, and 19 (17.9%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.1.<ref name=DP1/> There were 61 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (57.5% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Mountain Ranch CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0649628 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 29, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 27 people (12.1%) under the age of 18, 3 people (1.3%) aged 18 to 24, 46 people (20.6%) aged 25 to 44, 51 people (22.9%) aged 45 to 64, and 96 people (43.0%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 59.9{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 84.3 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 145 housing units at an average density of {{convert|37.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 106 (73.1%) were occupied. Of these, 81 (76.4%) were owner-occupied, and 25 (23.6%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] Mountain Ranch had a population of 1,628. The population density was {{convert|39.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Mountain Ranch was 1,472 (90.4%) White, 15 (0.9%) African American, 33 (2.0%) Native American, 18 (1.1%) Asian, 2 (0.1%) Pacific Islander, 15 (0.9%) from other races, and 73 (4.5%) from two or more races.  Hispanic or Latino of any race were 123 people (7.6%).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0649628|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715031914/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0649628|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Mountain Ranch CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households, no one lived in non-institutionalized group quarters and no one was institutionalized.

There were 748 households, 113 (15.1%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 410 (54.8%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 53 (7.1%) had a female householder with no husband present, 23 (3.1%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 50 (6.7%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 5 (0.7%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 211 households (28.2%) were one person and 89 (11.9%) had someone living alone who was 65 or older. The average household size was 2.18.  There were 486 families (65.0% of households); the average family size was 2.60.

The age distribution was 213 people (13.1%) under the age of 18, 86 people (5.3%) aged 18 to 24, 201 people (12.3%) aged 25 to 44, 712 people (43.7%) aged 45 to 64, and 416 people (25.6%) who were 65 or older.  The median age was 55.3 years. For every 100 females, there were 105.8 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 106.3 males.

There were 960 housing units at an average density of 23.3 per square mile (9.0/km{{sup|2}}), of which 748 were occupied, 620 (82.9%) by the owners and 128 (17.1%) by renters.  The homeowner vacancy rate was 2.8%; the rental vacancy rate was 9.8%.  1,352 people (83.0% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 276 people (17.0%) lived in rental housing units.

